<title>UK: P&amp;U sees no further job losses.</title>
<headline>P&amp;U sees no further job losses.</headline>
<dateline>LONDON 1997-04-29</dateline>
<text>
<p>Swedish-U.S. drug group Pharmacia &amp; Upjohn Inc said on Tuesday that no further job cuts were expected as a result of its disappointing first-quarter results.</p>
<p>Speaking to journalists in a conference call, board chairman Richard Brown said, &quot;There is no indication at this point that there will be any more reductions of the workforce anywhere in the world.&quot;  </p>
<p>Brown said that the group's board remained &quot;solidly behind the merger&quot;.</p>
<p>&quot;It made sense when we agreed to do it and it makes as much sense today,&quot; Brown told reporters.</p>
<p>&quot;We are not satisfied by the financial results that this company has just announced,&quot; he added. &quot;The board remains absolutely committed to the enhancement of long-term shareholder value of this company.&quot;</p>
<p>Pharmacia &amp; Upjohn repeated its intention of divesting the Plasma business and said it was considering &quot;strategic alternatives&quot; for its biotech business.</p>
<p>--London Newsroom +44 171 542 7717</p>
